## 3️⃣ Basic ModelAdmin — Customising the List View

Without customisation, admin shows this:

```
Posts
──────────────
Post object (1)
Post object (2)
Post object (3)
```

Let's fix it:

```python
# blog/admin.py
from django.contrib import admin
from .models import Post

@admin.register(Post)  # cleaner than admin.site.register()
class PostAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):

    list_display       = ['title', 'author', 'is_published', 'created_at']
    list_filter        = ['is_published', 'created_at', 'author']
    search_fields      = ['title', 'content', 'author__username']
    ordering           = ['-created_at']
    list_per_page      = 25
    list_display_links = ['title']       # clicking title opens detail page
    list_editable      = ['is_published'] # edit this column directly in list
```

### List View Options at a Glance

| Option | What It Does |
|--------|-------------|
| `list_display` | Columns shown in list view |
| `list_filter` | Sidebar filter panel |
| `search_fields` | Enables the search box |
| `ordering` | Default sort order |
| `list_per_page` | Items per page |
| `list_display_links` | Which column links to detail page |
| `list_editable` | Columns editable directly in list |

