## 4️⃣ Customising the Detail / Edit View

```python
@admin.register(Post)
class PostAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):
    list_display = ['title', 'author', 'is_published', 'created_at']

    # Simple flat field list:
    fields = ['title', 'content', 'author', 'is_published']

    # OR use fieldsets for grouped layout (better for complex forms):
    fieldsets = [
        ('Post Information', {
            'fields': ['title', 'content']
        }),
        ('Publishing', {
            'fields': ['is_published', 'author'],
            'classes': ['collapse'],
            'description': 'Control publishing settings here'
        }),
        ('Metadata', {
            'fields': ['created_at', 'updated_at'],
            'classes': ['collapse']
        }),
    ]

    readonly_fields      = ['created_at', 'updated_at', 'slug']
    prepopulated_fields  = {'slug': ('title',)}  # auto-fills slug from title
    filter_horizontal    = ['tags']              # better UI for ManyToMany
    raw_id_fields        = ['author']            # for ForeignKey with many options
```

### `fields` vs `fieldsets`

| Option | Use For |
|--------|---------|
| `fields` | Simple list of fields to show, no grouping |
| `fieldsets` | Group fields into named sections — better for complex forms |

